news.title: Germany's PBB not to take on new business in USA, citing volatility
news.para: The lender, also known as PBB, said it would evaluate "all options" for its existing U.S. business, without elaborating. The U.S. is PBB's second biggest market, making up 14% of its loan portfolio.

news.title: Shree Cement's profit declines 16% to ₹556 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: ​Revenue from operations was higher at Rs 5,240 crore in Q4 FY25, up from Rs 5073 crore in the year-ago quarter, while the EBITDA remained steady at Rs 1,381 crore, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Fitch downgrades China Vanke further on liquidity concerns
news.para: Fitch downgraded long-term foreign- and local-currency issuer default ratings (IDRs) for the embattled property developer to 'CCC+' from 'B-'.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's profit falls 12% to ₹25.28 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Total income fell to Rs 153.69 crore in the fourth quarter of the current fiscal from Rs 234.08 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Keystone Realtors' profit up 69% to ₹188 crore in FY25
news.para: The company's total income, however, declined to Rs 642.20 crore in January-March period of the last fiscal from Rs 826.15 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Thailand: Frasers Property makes second try to take REIT private in $1 billion deal
news.para: The billionaire's family and Frasers Property already own a little over 60% of the hospitality real estate investment trust's (REIT) units, and have offered S$0.71 for each unit they do not own.

news.title: Law soon to regularise houses on comunidade, alvara & private land: Goa CM
news.para: Pramod Sawant said govt is not interested in demolishing any houses and that any such recent demolitions have taken place based on court orders only. He also said there is no reason why anyone’s home, which has existed in a land for decades, should face sudden demolition.

news.title: Intra-district property registrations in Maharashtra cross 1,000 in just two weeks
news.para: The initiative, introduced by the property registration department, allows people to register property at any sub-registrar office within a district, regardless of the property's actual location.

news.title: Stamp duty collections in Nagpur fall seven per cent short of target for FY25
news.para: Sources said the dip in collections indicates that real estate transactions did not align with the government's expectations.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to grant permit to high rise building plans within 72 hrs
news.para: A special cell will be established at the directorate of town and country planning (DTCP) office to oversee the grant of development permissions for such projects.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves ₹1,000 stamp duty for Nagpur smart city-hit homes
news.para: As per the decision, only Rs1,000 stamp duty will be levied for the registration of lease deeds for 28 houses allocated in Mouza Punapur to families displaced by the Smart City project.

news.title: Bengaluru: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout allottees walk out of meeting over commissioner 'downplaying issues'
news.para: The forum members accused BDA commissioner N Jayaram of downplaying the layout's deep-rooted issues and silencing those who have been demanding better facilities.

news.title: No registry for six years, homebuyers of Mahagun Mirabella move Allahabad HC
news.para: Over 500 families that have moved into the society paid anywhere between Rs 60 lakh and Rs 1.25 crore for their flats, but say they can't call it home yet without the papers.

news.title: CBI seeks land allotment files, maps, lease deeds for four societies from YEIDA
news.para: On April 29, the Supreme Court directed CBI to set up a special investigation team (SIT) to investigate an alleged builder-bank nexus that is suspected to have misused the subvention scheme to facilitate large-scale misappropriation of funds at the expense of homebuyers.

news.title: SC stays demolition of homes, commercial property in Chandni Chowk
news.para: The MCD was directed to file a status report with all details failing which the court warned it of contempt action or drawing an inference that they were in cahoots with the builders.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust's operating income up 7% to ₹447 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: According to a regulatory filing, the company declared distribution of Rs 303 crore or Rs 2 per unit to unitholders for the fourth quarter of 2024-25 fiscal.

news.title: Ramky Estates enters Mumbai with 1.5-acre slum redevelopment in Chembur
news.para: The project with development potential of around 463,000 sq ft including 237,000 sq ft free sale area for the developer holds a revenue potential of over Rs 550 crore.

news.title: Pune: A year after filing PT3 forms, many property owners await 40% tax sop
news.para: Kothrud resident Manasi Kulkarni said people were made to run from pillar to post to fill the forms last year. "But the discount has not been reflected. Now, we have been left hanging in balance about our property tax payment," she said.
